                    <msContents>
                        <summary><title type="uniform" xml:lang="en">The Revelations of Saint
                                Birgitta of Sweden, Book II</title>
                            <title type="uniform" xml:lang="la">Revelationes sancte Birgitte, Liber
                                II</title>. Together with <ref>Danish National Archives, E 338</ref>
                            these fragments were once part of the same codex. Dating from the second
                            half of the fifteenth century the fragments that comprise <ref>AM 1056
                                4to</ref> include some of the few extant translations into Old
                            Danish from Latin of <name type="person">St Birgitta of Sweden</name>'s
                            'Book of Revelations' ('Liber Celestis Reuelacionum'). The other
                            fragments of St Birgitta's Revelations in Old Danish are: <ref type="ms" target="#AM08-079-gamma-en">AM 79 I γ 8vo</ref>; <ref>The National
                                Archives of Norway, No. 84</ref>, and the previously mentioned
                                <ref>Danish National Archives, E 338</ref>.</summary>
